
Overview of noun ceiling

The noun ceiling has 4 senses (first 3 from tagged texts)
                                        
1. (7) ceiling -- (the overhead upper surface of a covered space; "he hated painting the ceiling")
2. (3) ceiling -- ((meteorology) altitude of the lowest layer of clouds)
3. (2) ceiling, roof, cap -- (an upper limit on what is allowed; "he put a ceiling on the number of women who worked for him"; "there was a roof on salaries"; "they established a cap for prices")
4. ceiling -- (maximum altitude at which a plane can fly (under specified conditions))
